    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-06T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="528"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5331/139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-06T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 6, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 6—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Department’s telegram No. 3, April 5, 5 p.m. Misleading newspaper accounts
                    referred to in my telegram 5, April 4, 11 a.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d528fn9">Not
                        printed; it reported that the newspapers merely published brief factual
                        accounts of the exclusion of Portugal from benefits from the Belgian
                        treaty.</note> were all based on Havas telegram from Washington. Have
                    carried out Department’s instruction by explaining situation to the Secretary
                    General of Ministry of Foreign Affairs, who will issue suitable statement to
                    press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
